    "128749238": {
      "title": "A soil column apparatus for laboratory infiltration study",
      "abstract": "This paper describes a large-scale soil column apparatus, the procedures for constructing the soil column, and the performance of the apparatus. The aim is to describe an apparatus that is capable of performing comprehensive infiltration studies rather than to describe one particular infiltration study or phenomenon. By using the apparatus, all the variables (pore-water pressures, water contents, inflow rate, and outflow rate) in an infiltration process can be measured instantaneously and automatically, and all the boundary conditions can be controlled. Major instruments of the soil column apparatus include a tensiometer-transducer system, data acquisition system, time-domain reflectometry, and electronic weighing balance. By using these instruments, relationships of the volumetric water content vs. matric suction of the soil and the infiltration rate vs. time at any point of time during an infiltration test can be obtained. Test results also show that the setup functioned properly and suggest that infiltration behavior of any soil configuration (single, 2-layered, or multilayered soil) can be studied using this apparatus for different infiltration rates."
    }
